<h2 id="reset-an-authorization">Reset an authorization</h2>

<p>OAuth applications can use this API method to reset a valid OAuth token without end user involvement. Applications must save the ‚Äútoken‚Äù property in the response, because changes take effect immediately. You must use <a href="https://developer.github.com/v3/auth#basic-authentication">Basic Authentication</a> when accessing it, where the username is the OAuth application <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">client_id</code> and the password is its <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">client_secret</code>. Invalid tokens will return <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">404 NOT FOUND</code>.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>POST /applications/:client_id/tokens/:access_token

</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="response-9">Response</h3>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>Status: 200 OK

</code></pre></div></div>

